                  <lb/>P O E M S
                                             <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <hi rend="small">on the
                                                  <lb/>
                     <lb/>
                     <emph>NAMING OF
                                        PLACES.</emph>
                  </hi>
               </titlePart>
            </docTitle>
         </titlePage>
         <pb n="176"/>
         <pb n="177"/>
         <argument xml:id="ARGUnp">
            <head>
               <lb/>
               <lb/>ADVERTISEMENT. </head>
            <p>By Persons resident in the country and attached to rural
                                   <lb/>objects, many places will be found unnamed or of
                                   <lb/>unknown names, where little Incidents will have
                                   <lb/>occurred, or feelings been experienced, which will have
                                   <lb/>given to such places a private and peculiar interest.
                                   <lb/>From a wish to give some sort of record to such
                                   Inci-<lb/>dents or renew the gratification of such Feelings,
                                   Names <lb/>have been given to Places by the Author and some of
                                   <lb/>his Friends, and the following Poems written in
                                   con-<lb/>sequence. </p>
         </argument>
         <pb n="178"/>
      </front>
